    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Shiloh is a small yet historically rich borough in Cumberland County, New Jersey.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/shiloh-nj-community-overview/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Originally called Cohansey Corners, the settlement was named after the nearby Cohansey River that powered early transport and farming.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/shiloh-nj-community-overview/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Much of Shiloh’s housing was built before World War II, giving the borough a charming historic appeal that stands out today.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/shiloh-nj-community-overview/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Shiloh Seventh Day Baptist Church, founded in the early days, remains the heart of the borough’s religious heritage.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/shiloh-nj-community-overview/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Shiloh’s formal establishment dates back to 1705, placing it among the oldest communities in the region.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/shiloh-nj-community-overview/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Local cultural influences shape Shiloh’s flavor, making the borough a unique blend of history and community spirit.",
